# Atlas-root working-tree cleanup (2026-07-06; chore commit retracted §A/§B of
# backlog ## Out-of-scope (explicit) ## Atlas-root working-tree dirty triage).
# `nul` line is defense in depth: the Windows-reserved-name on-disk file is
# un-deletable via Python `os.remove` / `shutil.rmtree` / `os.rename` on this
# build (PermissionError on the basename collision). The `.gitignore` pattern
# prevents any future reproduction from re-entering `git status --others`.
nul
script.py
repos/SynthSeg/
repos/report/

# Local linked-worktree lanes and dependency junctions. All Rust builds use the
# shared D:/atlas/target directory; per-worktree target trees are disposable.
worktrees/

# Atlas-root transient scratch artifacts (NOT gitlinked; created during chore ceremony)
# `_*` catch-all catches session-work scratch (e.g. `_de-dup-audit.txt`,
# `_e0599-*.txt`, `backlog-section-enum.txt`); the existing patterns cover
# `.body-scratch-*` / `.tmp-*` / `.verify-*.sh` / `errors[0-9]*.txt` etc.
# `*.bak` catches editor/stream-edit backup files (e.g. `backlog.md.bullet.bak`).
_*
*.bak
.body-scratch-*
.tmp-*
.verify-*.sh
ritk_errors.txt
errors.txt
errors[0-9]*.txt
cargolog*.txt
*.stderr
repos/leoneuro-rs/

